cs.GR, cs.CE, cs.MM, cs.CV, cs.DL

Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of software for visualizing complex 3-dimensional molecular structures, which falls under computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV). The use of software in chemistry also falls under computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE). The paper also mentions the use of chemical images as the basis of artworks, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) and deep learning (cs.DL) if machine learning techniques were used to generate the images.
